oai_dc:dc.dc:title: THE COMPLIMENTARY INTERACTION BETWEEN BEACH NOURISHMENT AND HARBOUR MANAGEMENT: FOUR CASES IN SPAIN
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Krueger, Gregorio Gomez-Pina
Ramirez, Jose L.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: case study
beach nourishment
harbor management
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This paper describes several results on beach nourishment and harbour management interaction, within the authors' area of responsibility. These positive results show the socio-economic benefits which can be achieved through effectively combining harbour and coastal requirements.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 24 (1994): Proceedings of 24th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Kobe, Japan, 1994.
